```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "scheduler": "SLURM",
    "nodes": 4,
    "cores": 4,
    "memory": "120GB",
    "partition": "qTRD",
    "time": "20:00:00",
    "job_name": "PRP4078",
    "error_file": "/data/users2/jwardell1/nshor_docker/examples/ds004078-project/jobs/error%A_%a.err",
    "output_file": "/data/users2/jwardell1/nshor_docker/examples/ds004078-project/jobs/out%A_%a.out",
    "account": "psy53c17",
    "mail_type": "ALL",
    "mail_user": "jwardell1@student.gsu.edu",
    "oversubscribe": true,
    "singularity_version": "3.10.2",
    "singularity_image": "/data/users2/jwardell1/nshor_docker/dkrimg.sif",
    "script_name": "pd_dockerParallelized.sh",
    "run_bind_point": "/data/users2/jwardell1/nshor_docker",
    "sub_paths_file": "/data/users2/jwardell1/nshor_docker/examples/ds004078-project/ds004078/paths"
  }
}
```

This script utilizes SLURM, a job scheduler, for resource management. It allocates 4 nodes, each with 4 cores, 120GB of memory, and runs for a maximum of 20 hours. The script is named "PRP4078" and uses the "qTRD" partition. The script also loads the Singularity container runtime (version 3.10.2) and executes the script "pd_dockerParallelized.sh" within the "dkrimg.sif" container.  It utilizes the "singularity exec" command to run the script within the container environment and maps specific directories within the host system (e.g., /data/users2/jwardell1/nshor_docker) to locations within the container.
